
[1]disregard

   DISREGARD, n. [dis and regard.] Neglect; omission of notice; slight;
   implying indifference or some degree of contempt; as, to pass one with
   disregard.

   DISREGARD, v.t. To omit to take notice of; to neglect to observe; to
   slight as unworthy of regard or notice.

   Studious of good, man disregarded fame.

   We are never to disregard the wants of the poor, nor the admonitions of
   conscience.
